# Default ingest whitelist — covers the canonical layout of an
# ITK external remote module.  Used by `ingest-module-v4.sh` for
# any module that does not provide an explicit `--whitelist`.
#
# filter-repo's `--paths-from-file` silently ignores paths that do
# not exist in a given upstream tree, so this single file is safe
# to apply across modules with assorted layouts (header-only,
# header+src, with-or-without-wrapping, etc.).
#
# Per-module quirks (e.g. an upstream `CMakeLists.txt` that carries
# bespoke find_package machinery conflicting with ITK's in-tree
# build) should be handled inside `ingest-module-v4.sh` via flags
# or a follow-up sanitizer pass, NOT by maintaining a separate
# per-module whitelist.

# Public headers
include

# Source (optional — header-only modules will simply have no match)
src

# Tests + fixtures
test

# Python wrapping
wrapping

# CMake / module metadata
CMakeLists.txt
itk-module.cmake
